ing for a concrete wrapper that implements `IFileSystem` and delegates to `System.IO` calls. But that's essentially what the `FileSystem` class from the package already does. I'm not entirely sure what gap they're trying to fill here. That said, they explicitly mentioned they already use `IFileSystem` from `System.IO.Abstractions` everywhere in their codebase, so creating a replacement interface seems counterintuitive. I should probably just ask for clarification on what they're actually trying to achieve here.","outputTokens":1113,"requestId":"3409:3BFDE:DF2279:1048AFC:69F4098D"},"id":"055d28dc-2c59-4709-a987-9d228eac71a0","timestamp":"2026-05-01T02:02:14.351Z","parentId":"19fee46b-49ff-4437-a9b7-5beaf81cacc7"}
